rca of the issue:
BUG: Hero count-up stuck at 0.
Reproduction: Open landing page → wait 2-3s → inspect proof tile (right side of hero). Both large numerals show 0 instead of animating 0→47 and 0→5.
Root cause: useCountUp hook in /app/frontend/src/components/landing/Hero.jsx lines 16-34 uses `const ran = useRef(false)` + `if (ran.current) return; ran.current = true;` to dedupe, AND the effect cleanup runs `cancelAnimationFrame(raf)`. Under React 18 StrictMode (default in dev), every effect runs mount→cleanup→mount. First mount: ran.current=true, schedules RAF. Cleanup: cancelAnimationFrame kills the only RAF. Second mount: short-circuits because ran.current is already true. Net: setV(end) never fires, value stays at start (0).
Mitigation: Remove the `ran.current` guard entirely (cleanup already handles cancellation idempotently — t0 just resets on remount which is harmless), OR reset ran.current=false in the cleanup function. Simpler patch:
  useEffect(() => {
    const t0 = performance.now();
    let raf = 0;
    const tick = (now) => { ... };
    raf = requestAnimationFrame(tick);
    return () => cancelAnimationFrame(raf);
  }, [end, durationMs, start]);
